<!--
  Driveway Lighting Automation
  ============================
  Outdoor lighting scene triggered by ambient brightness + motion. Dims Hue
  floodlight + camera wallwashers automatically at dusk, then ramps to bright
  scene + camera frontlights when motion is detected by either a Hue PIR or
  one of two Bosch cameras. After a configurable timeout the lights fall back
  to the dimmed scene.

  Setup:
    1. Replace the eight placeholders below with your own object IDs:
         <CAM_UUID_1>          first  Bosch camera UUID
         <CAM_UUID_2>          second Bosch camera UUID
         <ILLUMINATION_SENSOR> lux datapoint (e.g. an HM-Sec-MDIR illumination
                               channel, hue motion sensor lightlevel, etc.)
         <HUE_FLOODLIGHT>      Hue lamp or group on/off datapoint
         <HUE_SCENE_DIMMED>    Hue scene (dimmed)  - boolean activator
         <HUE_SCENE_BRIGHT>    Hue scene (bright)  - boolean activator
         <HUE_PIR_1>           first  Hue outdoor motion sensor presence
         <HUE_PIR_2>           second Hue outdoor motion sensor presence
       Remove the second-camera or second-PIR branches if you have fewer
       devices.
    2. Tweak the lux threshold (default: 20) and timeout duration to taste.
    3. Save + Run the script.

  Contributed by Jaschkopf via
  https://forum.iobroker.net/topic/84538/adapter-bosch-smart-home-kameras/29
  (post #29, 2026-05-19). Placeholders replace the original user-specific
  object IDs; logic preserved verbatim.
-->
